Introduction

Cho HaSeul is a South Korean singer-songwriter under MODHAUS, known for her role as a member of the project girl group ARTMS. She is also the leader of the girl group LOONA and its first sub-unit, LOONA 1/3. HaSeul debuted as a member of LOONA on December 8, 2016, and later released her solo single album "HaSeul" on December 15, 2016.

HaSeul developed a passion for singing in elementary school and refined her skills while studying abroad in Australia and the USA. Initially planning to study opera, she was discovered by BlockBerryCreative after a singing contest and became a trainee in late 2015. After a year of training, she was selected as the third member of LOONA, despite having no prior dance experience and making mistakes during choreography.

HaSeul was revealed as the third member of LOONA on December 8, 2016, with the release of the second “Who’s Next Girl?” teaser. She officially debuted with the group on August 20, 2018. During her time in LOONA, HaSeul took a hiatus due to anxiety, lasting from January 7, 2020, to June 2, 2021.
